Sentencas: A Ni-free solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) ceramic anode composed of CoFe alloy (CFA) nanoparticles evenly dispersed in porous Ruddlesden-Popper-type layered oxide Gd2SrCo0.8Fe1.2O7-delta (RP-GSCF) has been fabricated by an in situ reduction method.
Titulo: In Situ Exsolved CoFe Alloy Nanoparticles on Gd2SrCo0.8Fe1.2O7-δ for Direct Hydrocarbon Fuel Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The RP-GSCF-CFA anode demonstrates good catalytic activity toward H-2 and hydrocarbon fuels.
Titulo: In Situ Exsolved CoFe Alloy Nanoparticles on Gd2SrCo0.8Fe1.2O7-δ for Direct Hydrocarbon Fuel Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.83Mg0.17O3-delta (LSGM) electrolyte-supported single cell with RP-GSCF-CFA as the anode and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) as the cathode deliver a maximum power density of 0.45 and 0.34 W cm(-2) in humidified H-2 and CH4 at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: In Situ Exsolved CoFe Alloy Nanoparticles on Gd2SrCo0.8Fe1.2O7-δ for Direct Hydrocarbon Fuel Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the RP-GSCF-CFA anode demonstrates good stability in wet CH4 for over 72 h, indicating good coking resistance.
Titulo: In Situ Exsolved CoFe Alloy Nanoparticles on Gd2SrCo0.8Fe1.2O7-δ for Direct Hydrocarbon Fuel Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
